2026-02-23 | Union of Two Array

Question
Given arrays a[] and b[],
return their union (distinct elements only).

	Approach
1.	Use a hash set to store unique elements.
2.	Insert all elements from a[] into the set.
3.	Insert all elements from b[] into the set.
4.	Convert the set to a vector and return it.
5.	Time Complexity:
		O(n + m)
6.	Space Complexity:
		O(n + m)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> findUnion(vector<int>& a, vector<int>& b) {
        unordered_set<int> st;

        for (int x : a)
            st.insert(x);

        for (int x : b)
            st.insert(x);

        vector<int> result(st.begin(), st.end());
        return result;
    }
};

	Key Insight
A set automatically removes duplicates.
By inserting elements from both arrays,
we directly obtain the union in optimal linear time.
